  "text": "We next describe various curvature conditions that are related to nonnegative isotropic curvature, and are also preserved by the Ricci flow. The following is an immediate consequence of Theorem 5.2: Corollary 5.4 (S. Brendle, R. Schoen [CITATION_1] ). Let M be a compact manifold of dimension n ≥ 4, and let g(t), t ∈ [0, T ), be a solution to the Ricci flow on M . Then:",
